        {
          "text": "Here's the content of `notes/subagents.md` — a design document for a **sub-agent/delegation system** in the Nest application. Here's a summary of the key points:\n\n## Overview\nThe document describes a parent-child agent architecture where a running agent can spawn a child agent (via `clone_agent`) that inherits the parent's context and runs a delegated task. The parent blocks until the child completes.\n\n## Key Design Areas\n\n### 1. **Core Model**\n- Agents form a tree via `parent_id` field\n- `clone_agent` tool spawns a child with inherited context + new instruction\n- Parent's chat task blocks until child completes a full turn\n\n### 2. **Blocking Model**\n- Same pattern as compaction — chat task sends request to GenServer, blocks on `receive`\n- Child signals `{:child_completed, ...}` when going idle\n- Parent's chat task unblocks with the child's final message content\n\n### 3. **Token Tracking (3 concepts)**\n- **Context tokens** — per-call, what's sent to the LLM (already exists)\n- **Direct usage** — this agent's own LLM calls (current `usage_totals`)\n- **Total usage** — direct + all descendants' usage, recursively\n- Propagation flows up one level at a time (child sends `total_usage` to parent)\n\n### 4. **Recursion**\n- Children can spawn their own children\n- `depth` tracked on state; configurable max depth (default 3, stored in DotConfig)\n\n### 5. **Child Lifecycle**\n- Child stays alive after completion (user can inspect)\n- Cascade termination: stopping parent stops all children recursively\n- Stopping parent while waiting also stops the active child\n\n### 6. **UI Changes**\n- Agent list becomes a tree view (indented/collapsible)\n- \"Delegated Task\" card in parent's conversation (with status, link to child, response)\n- \"Back to parent\" navigation link on child's final message\n- Status broadcast extended with `descendantUsage` and `totalUsage`\n\n### 7. **Resolved Questions**\n- Max depth config lives in DotConfig\n- Parent cleanup is forceful (all children terminated)\n- Stopping parent also stops active child\n- Children inherit tools minus `clone_agent` if at max depth\n- `total_usage` (direct + descendant) sent at child completion\n\nThis is a comprehensive design doc ready for implementation. Want me to start planning or building any part of this?",
          "type": "text"
        },
